Galen Framework is an open-source tool for testing layout and responsive design of web applications.
For more information visit http://galenframework.com

usage: galen <action> [<args>]

The available galen actions are:
    test
    check
    dump
    config
    help
    version

test:
    Loads and executes galen tests in specified path

    usage: galen test <testpath> [--htmlreport] [--testngreport]  [--junitreport]
            [--jsonreport] [--parallel-suites <parallel-suites-number>]
            [--filter <test-filter>] [--recursive] [--groups <groups>]
            [--excluded-groups <excluded-groups>]
            [-D<property-name>=<property-value>]

check:
    Opens browser and performs layout check with specified spec

    usage: galen check <specpath>  --url <url> --size <size>
            [--htmlreport <htmlreportpath>] [--testngreport <testngpath>] [--junitreport <junitpath>]
            [--jsonreport <jsonpath>] [--javascript <jspath>]
            [--include <tags>] [--exclude <excluded-tags>]
            [-D<property-name>=<property-value>]

dump:
    Opens browser and create a page dump for a specified spec

    usage: galen dump <specpath> --url <url> --size <size> --export <export-path>
            [--max-width <max-width>] [--max-height <max-height>]


